Zoophagia is a fictional psychological condition with which the character Renfield is afflicted in the novel Dracula. The condition is named by Dr. Seward and consists of the belief that if you eat live animals you gain their lifeforce onto your own.
The way Renfield attempts to extend his own life is that he gathers a great many flies then gathers a great number of spiders whom he feeds the flies to. The spiders are then fed to a great number of sparrows... He only ever got as far as the sparrows in the novel however. He almost got a cat from Dr. Seward (who was fascinated by the experiment), but never did. At many points the cycle is interrupted and he is forced to devour all in a hurry.
Whether the Zoophagia was caused by Renfield's servitude to Dracula or was a preexisting condition which made him more succeptible to the Count's power is never revealed.